Available Tools: select_records | select_with_filter | select_with_join | count_records
Call Schema: { "func_call": "string", "table": "string", "columns": ["string"], "where": "string", "limit": number }
Response Schema: { "rows": [{}], "count": number, "query_ms": number }
---
Question: Join users and orders to find the names and order dates for the first 5 customers who placed an order.
Call: { "func_call": "select_with_join", "table": "users", "columns": ["users.name", "orders.order_date"], "where": "users.id = orders.user_id", "limit": 5 }
Response: { "rows": [{"name": "Alice Johnson", "order_date": "2023-10-01"}, {"name": "Bob Smith", "order_date": "2023-10-02"}, {"name": "Charlie Brown", "order_date": "2023-10-03"}, {"name": "Diana Prince", "order_date": "2023-10-04"}, {"name": "Evan Wright", "order_date": "2023-10-05"}], "count": 5, "query_ms": 12 }
