Question: Select user emails and their total order value by joining users, orders, and order_items, limited to the top 10 spenders.
Call: { "func_call": "select_with_join", "table": "users", "columns": ["users.email", "SUM(order_items.price * order_items.quantity) as total_spent"], "where": "users.id = orders.user_id AND orders.id = order_items.order_id", "limit": 10 }
Response: { "rows": [{"email": "richard@techcorp.com", "total_spent": 15400.50}, {"email": "sarah@designs.net", "total_spent": 12300.00}, {"email": "mike@startups.io", "total_spent": 9850.25}], "count": 3, "query_ms": 45 }
